display="inline"><![CDATA[u\colon  X\to  Y]]></fr:tex> be a continuous map between topological spaces.
    We say that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[u]]></fr:tex> is <fr:em>proper</fr:em> if it is proper in the sense of Bourbaki (i.e. universally closed) and furthermore separated (i.e. the diagonal of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[X\times _Y X]]></fr:tex> is closed).</fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree><fr:tree
