xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>2050</fr:anchor><fr:addr
type="user">hodge-theory-iii-0.4</fr:addr><fr:route>hodge-theory-iii-0.4.xml</fr:route><fr:authors /><fr:number>III.0.4</fr:number><fr:parent>hodge-theory-iii-terminology-and-notation</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>A <fr:em>mixed Hodge <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex>-structure</fr:em> consists of an <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex>-module <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[H_A]]></fr:tex> of finite type, a finite increasing filtration <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[W]]></fr:tex> on the <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A\otimes \mathbb {Q}]]></fr:tex>-vector space <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[H_{A\otimes \mathbb {Q}}=H_A\otimes \mathbb {Q}]]></fr:tex>, and a finite decreasing filtration <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[F]]></fr:tex> on the <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {C}]]></fr:tex>-vector space <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[H_\mathbb {C}=H_A\otimes _A\mathbb {C}]]></fr:tex>.
    We demand that the <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[(\operatorname {Gr}_n^W(H_{A\otimes \mathbb {Q}}),\operatorname {Gr}_n^W(F))]]></fr:tex> be Hodge <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A\otimes \mathbb {Q}]]></fr:tex>-structures.
    For <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A=\mathbb {Z}]]></fr:tex> (resp. <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A=\mathbb {Q}]]></fr:tex>), we recover <fr:ref
addr="hodge-theory-ii-2.3.1"
href="hodge-theory-ii-2.3.1.xml"
taxon="Definition"
number="2.3.1" /> (resp. <fr:ref
addr="hodge-theory-ii-2.3.8"
href="hodge-theory-ii-2.3.8.xml"
number="2.3.8" />);
    the results of <fr:ref
addr="hodge-theory-ii-2.3"
href="hodge-theory-ii-2.3.xml"
number="2.3" /> carry over as they are.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree><fr:tree
