xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>2078</fr:anchor><fr:addr
type="user">hodge-theory-ii-3.1.2</fr:addr><fr:route>hodge-theory-ii-3.1.2.xml</fr:route><fr:authors /><fr:number>3.1.2</fr:number><fr:parent>hodge-theory-ii-3.1</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>A divisor <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[Y]]></fr:tex> in a smooth complex analytic variety <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> is said to be of <fr:em>normal crossing</fr:em> if the inclusion of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[Y]]></fr:tex> into <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> is locally isomorphic to the inclusion of a union of coordinate hyperplanes in <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {C}^n]]></fr:tex>;
    this does not imply that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[Y]]></fr:tex> is the union of smooth divisors.
    Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[Y]]></fr:tex> be a normal crossing divisor in <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex>, and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[j]]></fr:tex> the inclusion of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[X^*=X\setminus  Y]]></fr:tex> into <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex>.
    We denote by <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\Omega _X^1\langle  Y\rangle ]]></fr:tex> the locally free sub-<fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {O}]]></fr:tex>-module of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[j_*\Omega _{X^*}^1]]></fr:tex> generated by <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\Omega _X^1]]></fr:tex> and the <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathrm {d} z_i/z_i]]></fr:tex> for <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[z_i]]></fr:tex> local coordinates of a local irreducible component of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[Y]]></fr:tex>.
    The <fr:em>sheaf <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\Omega _X^p\langle  Y\rangle ]]></fr:tex> of differential <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[p]]></fr:tex>-forms on <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> with logarithmic poles along <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[Y]]></fr:tex></fr:em> is by the definition the locally free sub-sheaf <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\wedge ^p\Omega _X^1\langle  Y\rangle ]]></fr:tex> of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[j_*\Omega _{X^*}^p]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree></fr:backmatter></fr:tree>